In [[dynamical systems theory]], the '''Bogdanov map''' is a [[chaos theory|chaotic]] 2D map related to the [[Bogdanov–Takens bifurcation]]. It is given by the transformation:
:<math> \begin{cases} x_{n+1} = x_n + y_{n+1}\\ y_{n+1} = y_n + \epsilon y_n + k x_n (x_n - 1) + \mu x_n y_n \end{cases} </math>
The Bogdanov map is named after [[Rifkat Bogdanov]].
==See also== * [[List of chaotic maps]]
