In [[cryptography]], '''CryptMT''' is a [[stream cipher]] [[algorithm]] which internally uses the [[Mersenne twister]]. It was developed by [[Makoto Matsumoto]], [[Hagita Mariko]], [[Takuji Nishimura]] and [[Matsuo Saito]] and is [[patent]]ed. It has been submitted to the [[eSTREAM]] project of the [[eCRYPT]] network.
In that submission to [[eSTREAM]], the authors also included another cipher named '''Fubuki''', which also uses the Mersenne twister.
