In [[mathematical physics]], '''level spacing''' is the difference between [[consecutive]] elements in some set of [[real numbers]].  In particular, it is the difference between consecutive energy levels or [[eigenvalues]] of a [[matrix (mathematics)|matrix]] or linear operator.

